  'pizza-hut': "Pizza Hut is an American multinational pizza restaurant chain. Famous for their Pan Pizza, their kitchens require extensive proofing protocols. Explore our insider guides on deep-dish prep, the dispatch system for delivery drivers, and oven management.",
  'popeyes': "Popeyes is an American multinational chain of fried chicken fast food restaurants. Their signature shatter-crunch crust comes from a labor-intensive hand-battering process. Learn why their kitchens often experience bottlenecks, how the battering station works, and their marination process.",
  'raising-canes': "Raising Cane's is an American fast-food chain specializing entirely in chicken fingers. Their hyper-focused menu allows for incredible kitchen efficiency. Read our guides on their proprietary sauce mixing, the 'Bird Specialist' role, and their continuous-flow frying strategy.",
  'shake-shack': "Shake Shack is an American fast casual restaurant chain that started as a hot dog cart. Now famous for premium smash burgers, their kitchens focus on quality crusts over speed. Discover the exact technique behind their flat-top smash, their proprietary meat blend, and bun toasting.",
  'sonic-drive-in': "Sonic Drive-In is an American drive-in fast-food restaurant chain. Operating with a massive menu and carhop service, their layout is unique. Learn how their switchboard routing system works, the logistics of carhop skating, and their extensive beverage mixing station.",
  'starbucks': "Starbucks is a multinational chain of coffeehouses and roastery reserves. Their behind-the-bar operations are heavily choreographed to handle massive volume. Dive into our guides on the Customer Support cycle, Frappuccino cold bar sequencing, and the reality of the 'Secret Menu'.",
  'subway': "Subway is a multinational fast food restaurant franchise that primarily sells submarine sandwiches. With the customer directly driving the assembly line, efficiency is key. Explore our guides on their bread baking proofers, the Bain fill line rules, and how to execute the perfect wrap fold.",
  'taco-bell': "Taco Bell is an American multinational chain of fast food restaurants serving Mexican-inspired food. Their kitchens are optimized for ridiculous speed using a standard ingredient matrix. Learn about the 'Linebacker' role, drive-thru timer hacks, and the hydration of their beans.",
  'waffle-house': "Waffle House is an American restaurant chain with locations largely in the South, famous for being open 24/7/365. Their unique ordering system relies entirely on physical markers on plates rather than printed tickets. Read our guide explaining the legendary 'Marking System'.",
  'wawa': "Wawa is an American chain of convenience stores and gas stations famous for its high-quality made-to-order hoagies. Their touch-screen ordering revolutionized the deli flow. Learn how their par-baked bread station and digital ticketing system manage morning rushes.",
  'wendys': "Wendy's is an American international fast food restaurant chain known for its square hamburgers. Their 'Fresh, Never Frozen' beef promise dictates a totally different supply chain and grill protocol than competitors. Discover how their 4-corner press works and how chili is made.",
  'whataburger': "Whataburger is an American regional fast food restaurant chain specializing in hamburgers. Their made-to-order model and extensive customization options require a highly adaptable grill line. Read our guides on their patty melt construction, Texas Toast preparation, and grill setup.",
  'white-castle': "White Castle is an American regional hamburger restaurant chain credited as the first fast-food chain in the US. Their square sliders are steam-grilled over a bed of onions rather than seared. Learn about their five-hole patty design and the unique mechanics of the steam grill.",
  'wingstop': "Wingstop is an American multinational chain of nostalgic, aviation-themed restaurants specializing in chicken wings. Their operation is surprisingly simple but highly focused. Explore our guides on their fry cook timing, the plain fry start, and the heavy toss-and-coat technique.",
  'zaxbys': "Zaxby's is an American chain of fast casual restaurants offering chicken wings, chicken fingers, and signature sauces. Their kitchen balances fried items with fresh salads. Read our guides on the composition of Zax Sauce, the ratio problem, and their breading station flow.",
  'applebees': "Applebee's is one of the largest casual dining chains in the world. Despite internet rumors about 'Chef Mike,' their kitchens balance genuine grill work with rapid-fire TurboChef ovens. Read our honest breakdown of what gets microwaved and what gets flame-grilled.",
  'bojangles': "Bojangles is a Southern fast food chain famous for its made-from-scratch biscuits and Cajun-seasoned fried chicken. Their 4:00 AM biscuit maker shift is legendary. Learn how they hand-cut, proof, and bake biscuits that are the foundation of their entire menu.",
  'buffalo-wild-wings': "Buffalo Wild Wings is a casual dining and sports bar chain specializing in chicken wings with over 20 signature sauces. Their sauce-tossing station is the heart of the kitchen. Discover how they fry, toss, and manage their massive sauce inventory.",
  'cava': "Cava is a fast-casual Mediterranean restaurant chain specializing in customizable grain bowls and pitas. Their three-zone assembly line is engineered for speed and portion precision. Learn how they push hundreds of bowls per hour during the lunch rush.",
  'chilis': "Chili's Grill & Bar is an American casual dining restaurant chain known for Baby Back Ribs and sizzling fajitas. Their ribs arrive pre-cooked and get finished on the grill with their signature glaze. Read our guide on their grill finishing technique.",
  'dutch-bros': "Dutch Bros Coffee is a drive-thru-only coffee chain known for its high-energy service and hyper-customized drinks. Their 'Linebuster' system processes cars faster than almost any beverage chain. Learn how their dual-lane drive-thru and drink coding system work.",
  'long-john-silvers': "Long John Silver's is the largest seafood fast-food chain in the United States. Their signature crispy batter requires a specialized 'swim and drop' frying technique. Read our guide on their fryer mechanics, oil management, and the intense Lent season rush.",
  'sweetgreen': "Sweetgreen is a fast-casual restaurant chain specializing in salads and warm bowls made with locally sourced ingredients. Their mixing station uses a precision 'vortex toss' technique. Learn how they handle 150+ salads per hour while preventing cross-contamination."
};

function slugifyChain(chain: string): string {
  return chain
    .toLowerCase()
    .replace(/[']/g, '')
    .replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g, '-')
    .replace(/^-|-$/g, '');
}


export async function getStaticPaths() {
  function slugifyChain(chain: string): string {
    return chain.toLowerCase().replace(/['']/g, '').replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g, '-').replace(/^-|-$/g, '');
  }
  const allPosts = await getCollection('articles');
  const chains = [...new Set(allPosts.map(p => p.data.chain).filter(Boolean))] as string[];

  return chains.map(chain => {
    const slug = slugifyChain(chain);
    const posts = allPosts
      .filter(p => p.data.chain === chain)
      .sort((a, b) => b.data.pubDate.valueOf() - a.data.pubDate.valueOf());

    return {
      params: { chain: slug },
      props: { chainName: chain, posts },
    };
  });
}

const { chainName, posts } = Astro.props;
const chainSlug = slugifyChain(chainName);
const displayName = chainMap[chainSlug] || chainName;
const chainDesc = chainDescriptions[chainSlug];
const metaDescription = chainDesc
  ? chainDesc.substring(0, 155) + (chainDesc.length > 155 ? '...' : '')
  : `Browse all insider guides for ${displayName}. Real tips from real workers.`;
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <BaseHead
    title={`${displayName} Guides | Fast Food Guides`}
    description={metaDescription}
    noindex={posts.length < 3}
  />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "CollectionPage",
    "name": `${displayName} Guides`,
    "description": metaDescription,
    "url": `https://fastfoodguides.com/articles/chain/${chainSlug}/`,
    "mainEntity": {
      "@type": "ItemList",
      "numberOfItems": posts.length,
      "itemListElement": posts.map((post, i) => ({
        "@type": "ListItem",
        "position": i + 1,
        "url": `https://fastfoodguides.com/articles/${post.id}/`,
        "name": post.data.title
      }))
    }
  })} />
</head>
<body>
  <Header />
  <main>
    <div class="chain-header">
      <a href="/articles/" class="back-link">← All Guides</a>
      <h1>{displayName} Guides</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">{posts.length} insider guide{posts.length !== 1 ? 's' : ''} from real {displayName} workers.</p>
      {chainDescriptions[chainSlug] && (
        <p class="chain-description">{chainDescriptions[chainSlug]}</p>
      )}
    </div>

    {posts.length >= 3 && (
      <div class="hub-content">
        <h2>What to Expect from {displayName} Operations</h2>
        <p>
          Unlike casual dining or full-service restaurants, {displayName} operates on a strictly optimized kitchen flow designed to maximize throughput during peak hours. Our insider guides below detail the exact stations, standard operating procedures, and unwritten rules that make {displayName} kitchens function. From prep routines to drive-thru timer management, these guides are based on real QSR experience.
        </p>
      </div>
    )}

    <div class="articles-grid">
      {posts.map((post) => (
        <a href={`/articles/${post.id}/`} class="article-card">
          <h3>{post.data.title}</h3>
          <p class="date"><FormattedDate date={post.data.pubDate} /></p>
          <p class="desc">{post.data.description}</p>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</body>
</html>

<style>
  body {
    background-color: #0a0f1c;
    color: #F1F5F9;
    min-height: 100vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  main {
    flex: 1;
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem 4rem;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .chain-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    color: #10B981;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }
  .back-link:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #F1F5F9, #94A3B8);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .subtitle {
    color: #94A3B8;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  .chain-description {
    color: #CBD5E1;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.05);
    border-left: 3px solid #0EA5E9;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .hub-content {
    background: #111827;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .hub-content h2 {
    color: #F1F5F9;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .hub-content p {
    color: #94A3B8;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .articles-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .article-card {
    display: block;
    background: #1a2332;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.75rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
  }
  .article-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    border-color: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.3);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 25px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
  }

  .article-card h3 {
    color: #10B981;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .date {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #64748B;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .desc {
    color: #94A3B8;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .articles-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
